{
  "stem": "10181.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Difficult to-- it was maybe-- the whole camp might have been the size of a big football field, maybe a little bit bigger, but there were 20,000 or 30,000 people at the time there.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "You know, so that's how confined it was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "You know, I mean, there was like a mass of people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And, of course, the-- the saddest thing was that every-- every-- nearly every week there was-- sometimes, there was a break.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "At one time, there was a break of a month or so, you know, for-- for whatever reason.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "It was more technical.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It wasn't that they didn't want to send the Jews away, there were other reasons for it, you know, within-- within the German system.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What-- what-- what was happening to the people once they left, we didn't know, because we were too far away.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, you hear stories-- stories of people living in the Warsaw ghetto who were taken to Treblinka, and they escaped and came back and warned the people in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But that was close by.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "People who were taken to Auschwitz from Holland had no way of-- of-- even if they weren't gassed right away, If they-- there was no way of-- even if they did escape, there was no way of making it back to Holland.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know that anybody did escape, any Dutch Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Maybe, maybe they didn't.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't know, but I mean, it was-- this was in Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was all of Germany in between, you know, so there wasn't a way of-- of, you know, finding out what it was all about.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was just a name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Auschwitz was a name.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "What people were afraid of were, like I told you, Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That was the fear.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So they weren't sent to Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were sent to Auschwitz, which was a labor camp, supposedly.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then, of course, more people came in from the outside, and they brought the news.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's how you knew what was happening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was your best-- usually the best sort of information, you know, people who knew people who came to the camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nine months, about, you know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After about nine months, they-- I can give you the exact date when we left.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was January 11, 1944.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was after nine months in Westerbork, and there were very few people left in the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were called to go on a train to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, the immigration to Palestine was very restricted, but they had got certificates to immigrate to Palestine, valid certificates.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they got them too late.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They-- they couldn't get to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember them well because we were-- at the time on that train, there were very few children.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know why.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Later on, families came.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But at that time-- and we were sitting on the train with some of these people, and they sort of tried to watch us a little bit, take care of us.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it took about two days to get to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Even though it wasn't that far, it took about two days.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When we got to Bergen-Belsen, the reception was sort of, you know, very scary because we arrived on the platform in a town called Celle, which is a sort of medieval town, which is I don't know how far, not that far, but far enough.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's how far the train went, and when you got to the platform, you had to-- the German-- you only had to-- you didn't have no longer any Dutch police.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Even though the Dutch police weren't any better, you felt better about it because they were Dutch, or-- or you had the Jewish police in Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There to meet us were just SS, you know, just the German guards, and we had to get off the train.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They made us, you know, stand in columns, and we started to walk into what's Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They had some trucks, but they put-- some things-- we were carrying things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They put it on there, and they put some-- some of the few women with little children on there also.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Even some people were afraid.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They didn't know what's gonna happen to them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They-- they went on there, and they were brought to the camp, you know, by truck.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And at the very beginning, when we got to Bergen-Belsen, what they did, we were standing there on role call to check out whether nobody had jumped off the train and all that.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they had these watchtowers where they used to fire-- they kept on firing in the air.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I think it was to scare us.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
